# Google Places API key (server-side). Powers two things:
#   - the address autocomplete on the quote form
#   - the live Google review rating + count (lib/rating.ts), cached daily
# 1. Google Cloud Console → create/select a project
# 2. Enable "Places API (New)" and enable Billing. Google no longer offers the
#    old flat $200/month credit; instead each SKU has a free monthly cap (e.g.
#    ~1,000 free Place Details calls/month for the rating tier). With daily
#    caching this project makes ~30 calls/month, so it stays free in practice.
# 3. Create an API key, restrict it to the Places API
# 4. Put it below in a file named .env.local (this file is only an example), and
#    add the same variable in your Vercel project settings for production.
# Until this is set, the address field falls back to a free (lower-quality)
# geocoder and the rating falls back to the hardcoded value in lib/site.ts.
GOOGLE_PLACES_API_KEY=

# GoHighLevel / Pest AI inbound-webhook URL. Estimate-form submissions POST to
# /api/lead, which forwards them here to create a CRM contact. In GHL: Automation
# → Workflows → new workflow → trigger "Inbound Webhook" → copy the URL. Treat it
# like a secret (put it here for local + in Vercel for prod, don't commit it).
# Until it's set, the form falls back to opening an email draft to the address
# above so no lead is lost.
GHL_WEBHOOK_URL=

# Vercel Blob — hosts the photos people attach to the estimate form. The form
# uploads them straight to Blob and passes the links along with the lead, so
# they show up on the CRM contact. Vercel adds this token automatically once you
# link a Blob store (Vercel dashboard → Storage → Create → Blob). Until it's set,
# the form still works — it just skips the photo links.
BLOB_READ_WRITE_TOKEN=

# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Analytics & marketing tags (all optional). Each tag only loads when its ID is
# set here (for local dev) and in the Vercel project settings (for production).
# Leave any of them blank to disable that tag. These are NEXT_PUBLIC_* because
# they run in the visitor's browser, so treat the values as public.
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------

# Microsoft Clarity — heat maps + session recordings (free, unlimited).
# Get it at https://clarity.microsoft.com → create a project for peakpestreno.com
# → Settings → Overview → copy the 10-character Project ID.
NEXT_PUBLIC_CLARITY_PROJECT_ID=

# Google Analytics 4 — traffic reporting (free).
# https://analytics.google.com → Admin → Data Streams → your web stream →
# copy the Measurement ID (looks like G-XXXXXXXXXX).
NEXT_PUBLIC_GA_MEASUREMENT_ID=

# Meta (Facebook/Instagram) Pixel — ad conversion tracking (free).
# https://business.facebook.com → Events Manager → your Pixel/dataset →
# Settings → copy the Pixel ID (a long number).
NEXT_PUBLIC_META_PIXEL_ID=
